Nick Clegg praised the courage of victims who spoke out
Times photographer, Paul Rogers
Roland Watson
Political Editor
Last updated at 10:29PM, September 28 2012
Nick Clegg has said that it is “completely unacceptable” for cultural sensitivities or political correctness to deter the pursuit of cases of child grooming.
The Deputy Prime Minister said that agencies across the country had failed to get a grip on the sexual exploitation of vulnerable young girls.
Police and social services should investigate without fear or favour, said Mr Clegg as he became the most senior politician to respond to the scale of the scandal exposed by The Times.
Mr Clegg also praised the courage of the victims of such abuse who had come forward to tell their stories
